OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1772204160
OL,3,CBlackpool's rough sleeping challenge:
OL,4,CWarm beds and rising numbers
OL,6,FThe Government's annual rough sleeping
OL,7,Fsnapshot is based on a single-night
OL,8,Fcount in autumn and provides a point-
OL,9,Fin-time estimate rather than a full
OL,10,Fannual total.
OL,12,FOn a single night in autumn 2025, the
OL,13,FGovernment's rough sleeping snapshot -
OL,14,Fwhich is based on a one-night count
OL,15,Fand captures only those seen or
OL,16,Fverified by outreach teams and local
OL,17,Fauthorities - recorded 4,793 people
OL,18,Fsleeping rough on the streets of
OL,19,FEngland, an increase of 78% from the
OL,20,F2,688 people that were counted in 2020.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/14
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
