OL,3,CBlackpool's rough sleeping challenge:
OL,4,CWarm beds and rising numbers
OL,6,FIn the North West, the number of rough
OL,7,Fsleepers recorded in the annual
OL,8,Fsnapshot has almost doubled when
OL,9,Fcompared to five years ago.
OL,11,FIn 2020, 226 people were recorded
OL,12,Fsleeping on the region's streets; that
OL,13,Ffigure has now risen to 441.
OL,15,FManchester recorded the highest number
OL,16,Fof rough sleepers in our region in the
OL,17,Flatest snapshot. Although 48 people
OL,18,Fwere counted on the night, this is
OL,19,Fsubstantially lower than the 123
OL,20,Frecorded on a single night in 2018.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/14
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
